e7eddbe12248c9/0_0_2560_1536/master/2560.jpg?width=645&amp;quality=85&amp;auto=format&amp;fit=max&amp;s=8710f0cb78ed2cc6ab898fced959d924 645w"><source media="(min-width: 0px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 0px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="465px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/b02aab80064d268957fdcb2d65e7eddbe12248c9/0_0_2560_1536/master/2560.jpg?width=465&amp;quality=45&amp;auto=format&amp;fit=max&amp;dpr=2&amp;s=89728aef76c6d860f28059fb6ba2eb46 930w"><source media="(min-width: 0px)" sizes="465px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/b02aab80064d268957fdcb2d65e7eddbe12248c9/0_0_2560_1536/master/2560.jpg?width=465&amp;quality=85&amp;auto=format&amp;fit=max&amp;s=c9bef4d8ae33466c0c922ffba1559a90 465w"><img class="maxed responsive-img" itemprop="contentUrl" alt="Left to right: midwife Safaa Alam and mental health nurse Lillian Mudzivare," src="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/b02aab80064d268957fdcb2d65e7eddbe12248c9/0_0_2560_1536/master/2560.jpg?width=300&amp;quality=85&amp;auto=format&amp;fit=max&amp;s=7de46b32690b9403b8be2c202d834b9a" style="border: 0px; display: block; width: 620px; height: 372px; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px;"></picture></div><span class="inline-expand-image inline-icon centered-icon rounded-icon article__fullscreen modern-visible" style="fill: rgb(255, 255, 255); border-radius: 62.5rem; display: inline-block; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0px; right: 0px; width: 2.75rem; height: 2.75rem; background-color: rgba(51, 51, 51, 0.6); margin: 0.625rem; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0.15s ease-out 0s;"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 22 22" class="centered-icon__svg rounded-icon__svg article__fullscreen__svg modern-visible__svg inline-expand-image__svg inline-icon__svg"><path d="M3.4 20.2L9 14.5 7.5 13l-5.7 5.6L1 14H0v7.5l.5.5H8v-1l-4.6-.8M18.7 1.9L13 7.6 14.4 9l5.7-5.7.5 4.7h1.2V.6l-.5-.5H14v1.2l4.7.6"></path></svg></span></a><figcaption class="caption caption--main caption--img" itemprop="description" style="max-width: none; padding: 0.5rem 0px 0.375rem; font-size: 0.75rem; line-height: 1rem; font-family: &quot;Guardian Text Sans Web&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, &quot;Lucida Grande&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(118, 118, 118); min-height: 0px;"><span class="inline-triangle inline-icon hide-until-tablet" style="fill: rgb(199, 0, 0);"><svg width="11" height="10" viewBox="0 0 11 10" class="hide-until-tablet__svg inline-triangle__svg inline-icon__svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.5 0L11 10H0z"></path></svg>&nbsp;</span>Left to right: midwife Safaa Alam and mental health nurse Lillian Mudzivare. Photograph: Birmingham Women\'s and Children\'s NHS Foundation Trust</figcaption></figure></header><div class="content__article-body from-content-api js-article__body" itemprop="articleBody" data-test-id="article-review-body" style="overflow-wrap: break-word; position: relative; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.5rem; font-family: &quot;Guardian Text Egyptian Web&quot;, Georgia, serif; margin-left: 0px; padding-bottom: 4.5rem; font-weight: 400;"><p style="padding: 0px;">A midwife and a mental health nurse from the same hospital trust have died after contracting coronavirus.</p><p style="padding: 0px;">Safaa Alam, 29, and Lillian Mudzivare, 42, both worked at&nbsp;<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk/birmingham" data-link-name="auto-linked-tag" data-component="auto-linked-tag" class="u-underline" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(171, 6, 19); cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid rgb(220, 220, 220); transition: border-color 0.15s ease-out 0s;">Birmingham</a>&nbsp;women’s and children’s NHS trust.</p><p style="padding: 0px;">Alam, whose father Mushtaq Afsar also died two weeks ago, was described as an “amazing midwife”. Her “skills and expertise helped to bring hundreds of new lives into the world”, said<a href="https://bwc.nhs.uk/news/tribute-to-safaa-alam-risk-management-midwife-2811" data-link-name="in body link" class="u-underline" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(171, 6, 19); cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid rgb(220, 220, 220); transition: border-color 0.15s ease-out 0s;">&nbsp;the trust’s chief executive, Sarah-Jane Marsh.</a></p><p style="padding: 0px;">In a statement, her husband Shazad said: “Saf was my beautiful and full of life wife.” He added they were childhood sweethearts, who grew up together, and their years together had been filled with “love, fun and adventure”.</p><p style="padding: 0px;">A&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gofundme.com/f/uncle-mushtaq-amp-his-beloved-daughter-safaa-alam?utm_medium=chat&amp;utm_source=whatsapp-visit&amp;utm_campaign=p_lico+share-sheet" data-link-name="in body link" class="u-underline" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(171, 6, 19); cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid rgb(220, 220, 220); transition: border-color 0.15s ease-out 0s;">Go Fund Me appeal</a>&nbsp;in memory of father and daughter has been set up. A bereavement notice on the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.facebook.com/JanazaAnnouncement/posts/1152793468419925" data-link-name="in body link" class="u-underline" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(171, 6, 19); cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid rgb(220, 220, 220); transition: border-color 0.15s ease-out 0s;">Janaza Announcement Facebook&nbsp;</a>page said Afsar died 14 days ago. “Sadly, his daughter Safaa, age 29, who is a midwife has also sadly passed away due to Covid-19”.</p><p style="padding: 0px;">Mudzivare, who lived with her husband, Moses, and their daughters in Birmingham, was a “much-loved member of our Forward Thinking Birmingham team whose bubbly, vibrant and bright approach touched the lives of everyone who knew her,” said Marsh.</p><p style="padding: 0px;">Staff paid tribute to her&nbsp;<a href="https://bwc.nhs.uk/news/tribute-to-lillian-mudzivare-senior-mental-health-nurse-2812" data-link-name="in body link" class="u-underline" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(171, 6, 19); cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid rgb(220, 220, 220); transition: border-color 0.15s ease-out 0s;">commitment to mental health and young people.</a></p><p style="padding: 0px;">In a statement, her family described her a “such a beautiful mother, wife and friend” and a “very proud nurse always caring for those who needed her help”.</p><figure class="element element-atom" data-atom-id="interactives/2020/03/covid-19-uk/default" data-atom-type="interactive" style="margin-top: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; position: relative;"><iframe class="interactive-atom-fence" height="272" style="width: 620px; border-width: 0px; border-style: initial;"></iframe></figure><p style="padding: 0px;">Four members of the trust’s staff have now died with Covid-19.</p><aside class="element element-rich-link element-rich-link--tag element--thumbnail element-rich-link--upgraded" data-component="rich-link-tag" data-link-name="rich-link-tag" style="float: left; margin: 0.3125rem 1.25rem 0.75rem -15rem; clear: left; width: 13.75rem;"><div class="rich-link tone-news--item rich-link--pillar-news" style="background-color: rgb(246, 246, 246); margin: 0px; position: relative; overflow: hidden;"><div class="rich-link__container" style="position: relative;"><div class="rich-link__image-container u-responsive-ratio" style="width: 220px; padding-bottom: 132px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; transition: background-color 0.25s ease 0s; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);"><img src="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/20141ae139806f124ead5f3792cccc18d2921d48/0_0_4000_2400/master/4000.jpg?width=460&amp;quality=85&amp;auto=format&amp;fit=max&amp;s=9ce88fe5f1e069cea6025887f5f61c2c" itemprop="contentURL" style="border: 0px; width: 220px; height: 132px; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px;"></div><div class="rich-link__header" style="font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.4375rem; font-family: &quot;Guardian Egyptian Web&quot;, Georgia, serif; padding: 0.125rem 0.3125rem 0.5em; min-height: 2.25rem;"><h2 class="rich-link__title" style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; padding: 0px;"><a class="rich-link__link" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; cursor: pointer;">Coronavirus: the week explained - sign up for our email newsletter</a></h2></div><div class="rich-link__read-more" style="padding-left: 0.3125rem;"><div class="rich-link__arrow" style="display: inline-block;"><span class="inline-arrow-in-circle inline-icon " style="fill: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="inline-arrow-in-circle__svg inline-icon__svg"><path class="rich-link__arrow-icon" d="M12 0C5.373 0 0 5.373 0 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12S18.627 0 12 0m.21 19l-.637-.668 4.888-6.326H4.996v-1.01h11.465l-4.888-6.333.637-.668L19 11.153v.685l-6.79 7.157" fill-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></span></div>&nbsp;<div class="rich-link__read-more-text" style="font-size: 0.875rem; font-family: &quot;Guardian Egyptian Web&quot;, Georgia, serif; display: inline-block; height: 1.875rem; line-height: 1.625rem; padding-left: 0.125rem; vertical-align: top; color: rgb(199, 0, 0);">Read more</div></div><a class="rich-link__link u-faux-block-link__overlay" href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/18/coronavirus-the-week-explained-sign-up-for-our-email-newsletter" aria-label="Coronavirus: the week explained - sign up for our email newsletter" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; color: inherit; cursor: pointer; top: 0px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; left: 0px; overflow: hidden; text-indent: 200%; white-space: nowrap; position: absolute; z-index: 0; opacity: 0;"></a></div></div></aside><p style="padding: 0px;">A care home director and her retired radiologist husband died with coronavirus in the same hospital 10 days apart. Dr James Oniah, 79, and his wife Mary (Nyirongo) Oniah, 61, who worked as a regional director for the Maria Mallaband Care Group (MMCG), lived in Ilford, east London, and died in the King George hospital in Redbridge. He was a director of the Onitsha Progressive Foundation, a charity for elderly diaspora from Onitsha, Nigeria. His wife trained in Zambia before coming to London to work as a midwife.</p><p style="padding: 0px;">A&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gofundme.com/f/in-memory-of-dr-james-and-mary-nyirongo-oniah" data-link-name="in body link" class="u-underline" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(171, 6, 19); cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid rgb(220, 220, 220); transition: border-color 0.15s ease-out 0s;">Go Fund Me appeal page</a>&nbsp;set up by the Zambians Together initiative said: “It is believed Mary contracted coronavirus in her line of duty as a regional director in care homes and sadly her husband James, a former doctor [radiologist] also contracted the disease.</p><p style="padding: 0px;">“They ended their fight for their lives against Covid-19 at King George’s hospital in London 10 days apart, leaving behind children and a wider network of family and friends who all considered them their mum and dad.”</p><p style="padding: 0px;">MMCG, which runs care homes across the UK, said: “Mary was a valued colleague and friend to many people in our company, she will be sorely missed. Our heartfelt sympathies go out to her family at this difficult time.”</p><p style="padding: 0px;">Tributes have also been paid to Andy Collier, 53, described as a “selfless” nurse practitioner at Hollins Park hospital in Warrington. The former rugby player, who died after testing positive for coronavirus, ran The First and Last pub in Leigh, with his wife, Carol. He had previously played for Wigan and Leigh Centurions rugby league sides. He was also a union representative for Unite and played golf at Leigh golf club.</p><p style="padding: 0px;">His ward manager, Rob Kelly, said: “He was very down-to-earth, fair and selfless.” He had been admitted to the Royal Albert Infirmary in Wigan after becoming seriously ill on 31 March.</p><p style="padding: 0px;">The chief executive at North West Boroughs Healthcare, Simon Barber, said: “It is clear he was a very dedicated and compassionate man. All our thoughts are with Andy’s family at this time and we offer them our sincere condolences.”</p><aside class="element element-rich-link element--thumbnail element-rich-link--upgraded" data-component="rich-link" data-link-name="rich-link-1 | 1" style="float: left; margin: 0.3125rem 1.25rem 0.75rem -15rem; clear: left; width: 13.75rem;"><div class="rich-link tone-feature--item rich-link--pillar-news" style="background-color: rgb(246, 246, 246); margin: 0px; position: relative; overflow: hidden;"><div class="rich-link__container" style="position: relative;"><div class="rich-link__image-container u-responsive-ratio" style="width: 220px; padding-bottom: 132px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; transition: background-color 0.25s ease 0s; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);"><img src="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/e2f05b088b21b204d29c106ed7059a4b17060e38/1253_753_2475_1485/master/2475.jpg?width=460&amp;quality=85&amp;auto=format&amp;fit=max&amp;s=099e22bed565d3292a9e6c058b14e818" itemprop="contentURL" style="border: 0px; width: 220px; height: 132px; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px;"></div><div class="rich-link__header" style="font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.4375rem; font-family: &quot;Guardian Egyptian Web&quot;, Georgia, serif; padding: 0.125rem 0.3125rem 0.5em; min-height: 2.25rem;"><h2 class="rich-link__title" style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; padding: 0px;"><a class="rich-link__link" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; cursor: pointer;">Doctors, nurses, porters, volunteers: the UK health workers who have died from Covid-19</a></h2></div><div class="rich-link__read-more" style="padding-left: 0.3125rem;"><div class="rich-link__arrow" style="display: inline-block;"><span class="inline-arrow-in-circle inline-icon " style="fill: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="inline-arrow-in-circle__svg inline-icon__svg"><path class="rich-link__arrow-icon" d="M12 0C5.373 0 0 5.373 0 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12S18.627 0 12 0m.21 19l-.637-.668 4.888-6.326H4.996v-1.01h11.465l-4.888-6.333.637-.668L19 11.153v.685l-6.79 7.157" fill-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></span></div>&nbsp;<div class="rich-link__read-more-text" style="font-size: 0.875rem; font-family: &quot;Guardian Egyptian Web&quot;, Georgia, serif; display: inline-block; height: 1.875rem; line-height: 1.625rem; padding-left: 0.125rem; vertical-align: top; color: rgb(199, 0, 0);">Read more</div></div><a class="rich-link__link u-faux-block-link__overlay" href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/16/doctors-nurses-porters-volunteers-the-uk-health-workers-who-have-died-from-covid-19" aria-label="Doctors, nurses, porters, volunteers: the UK health workers who have died from Covid-19" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; color: inherit; cursor: pointer; top: 0px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; left: 0px; overflow: hidden; text-indent: 200%; white-space: nowrap; position: absolute; z-index: 0; opacity: 0;"></a></div></div></aside><p style="padding: 0px;">Healthcare assistant Jun Terre, 52, who worked at Stoke Mandeville hospital died on 14 May, having tested positive for Covid-19. He was described as a “a gracious, quiet and kind gentleman with a smile that would light up a room”, by Neil Macdonald, Buckinghamshire healthcare&nbsp;<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/nhs" data-link-name="auto-linked-tag" data-component="auto-linked-tag" class="u-underline" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(171, 6, 19); cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid rgb(220, 220, 220); transition: border-color 0.15s ease-out 0s;">NHS</a>&nbsp;trust’s chief executive. His wife also works at the trust.</p><p style="padding: 0px;">The Labour MP for Slough, Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi, paid tribute to his uncle, taxi driver Satnam Singh Dhesi, 63, who died at Slough’s Wexham Park hospital, from Covid-19. He<a href="https://twitter.com/TanDhesi/status/1261006231751270403" data-link-name="in body link" class="u-underline" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(171, 6, 19); cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid rgb(220, 220, 220); transition: border-color 0.15s ease-out 0s;">&nbsp;posted on Twitter</a>: “My uncle, a fun-loving guy who never spoke ill of anyone, sadly contracted Covid and even a ventilator couldn’t save him. Tragically I could only see his funeral via Zoom.”</p><p style="padding: 0px;">Dhesi was a keen footballer and a regular helper and supporter at the Singh Sabha Football Academy in Slough, which had been co-founded by his son Harpreet. In April,&nbsp;<a href="https://twitter.com/TanDhesi/status/1253726167967899650" data-link-name="in body link" class="u-underline" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(171, 6, 19); cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid rgb(220, 220, 220); transition: border-color 0.15s ease-out 0s;">the MP posted he&nbsp;</a>had lost his grandmother to coronavirus.</p></div></div></div></div></header>',
